Sentencas: In this study, the physical properties of the Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-delta ceramics were measured and their potential for use as a cathode material of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) was evaluated.
Titulo: Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-δ ceramic as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A cubic phase was retained in all of the Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-delta ceramics.
Titulo: Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-δ ceramic as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Analysis of the temperature-dependent conductivity found the SrCo0.95Sn0.05O3-delta and Sr0.9Pr0.1Co0.95Sn0.05O3-delta ceramics exhibiting semiconductor-like behavior below 550 degrees C and metal-like behavior above the same temperature.
Titulo: Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-δ ceramic as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Sr0.8Pr0.2Co0.95Sn0.05O3-delta and Sr0.7Pr0.3Co0.95Sn0.05O3-delta ceramics, however, reported a metal-like conductivity in the whole temperature range.
Titulo: Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-δ ceramic as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of the Sr0.8Pr0.2Co0.95Sn0.05O3-delta ceramic at 500 degrees C and 700 degrees C read respectively 1250 S/cm and 680 S/cm, both of which were superior than those in most of the common perovslcites.
Titulo: Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-δ ceramic as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Single cells with a structure of NiO-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (SDC)/SDC/Sr0.8Pr0.2Co0.95Sn0.05O3-delta-SDC were built and characterized.
Titulo: Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-δ ceramic as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Addition of SDC in Sr0.8Pr0.2Co0.95Sn0.05O3-delta emerged to be a crucial factor reducing the ohmic resistance (R-o) and polarization resistance (R-p) of the cell by facilitating a better adhesion to and electrical contact with the electrolyte layer.
Titulo: Sr1-xPrxCo0.95Sn0.05O3-δ ceramic as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
